Studentlist

Visit website

The site is not well designed since there was not an implicit focus on the design but rather the functionality. The purpose of this project was to develop a student list with different features such as sorting, filtering, removing students from the list, adding them to the inquisitorial squad, etc. My main focus was implementing the features using JavaScript and more importantly to understand the logic behind programming with JavaScript. OBS! The site is a ‘hacked’ ... version, which is why it might seem like some of the functions do not work. I will recommend you to have a look at the code behind - or contact me so I can explain. Do not click on the student “Natalie Sirich” - a meme will appear and erase all other content on the site.

Campaign

Visit website

The idea behind this campaign for the NGO Rådet for Sikker Trafik, is to bring awareness about the importance of being visible in the traffic while riding a bicycle. The target audience is elderly people who either daily or weekly travel by bike. This project was focused on data analysis and online communication to a specific target audience. This target group in particular might be having a harder time using computers, so this was a point of emphasis for the design.

About me

About me

Studying to be a frontend developer

Natalie Sirich

I study multimedia design at KEA (Københavns Erhvervsakademi), with a goal of becoming a frontend developer. I am very passionate about webdesign, online communication and the technological development in society.

I am an ambitious woman with a natural flair for all things IT. I enjoy to taking action, and i work hard finding the perfect solutions for the specific client/case - both independently and with teams. I have a good attention to detail and i would describe myself as a good finisher. I am a very curious person who is eager to learn, discover new things and be inspired.

When it comes to design I like to keep things simple and focus on the message.
